com.neebal.android.simplyreliable.message

Interface BaseCallback

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    DeleteMessageCallback, GetMessageCallback, HeadMessageCallback, MultiPartGetMessageCallback, PostMessageCallback, PutMessageCallback, RedirectionCallback, StreamingResponseCallback

    public interface BaseCallback
extends Serializable
    A base interface that represents the various callbacks that can be called at the time of receiving a response from the server, for a particular type of Message
    Classes wishing to get a handle of the response must implement this callback. This interface will expose all the common methods that will be used at the time of receiving a response from the server.
    Since:
    1.4
    Author:
    Neebal Technologies
    See Also:
    StreamingResponseCallback, RedirectionCallback, GetMessageCallback, MultiPartGetMessageCallback, PostMessageCallback, PutMessageCallback, DeleteMessageCallback, HeadMessageCallback

        void handleErrorResponse(OutMessage outMessage,
                       String contentType,
                       String responseString,
                       int statusCode)
        Subclasses wishing to get a handle in case of an error, must write code in this method
        Parameters:
        outMessage - the OutMessage instance for which this callback is called
        contentType - the content type of the error response that is received
        responseString - the raw response string that describes the error
        statusCode - the raw low level http status code of this error response

        void handleMissingObjects(Map<String,Object> missingObjects)
        Subclasses wishing to get a handle of the missing objects that were returned from the other callbacks method of this interface, must override this method.
        Parameters:
        missingObjects - map of missing object names and the missing objects. It is the map that is returned from the other callback methods of this interface
